com.sap.conn.idoc.monitor

Interface IDocRepositoryMonitor


  • public interface IDocRepositoryMonitor
    An IDoc repository monitor provides some additional monitoring information about an IDocRepository instance.

    A central monitoring tool with no knowledge about the available repository instances can get access to all monitors as follows: 

        IDocFactory myFactory = ...;
    IDocRepository idocRepository;
    IDocRepositoryMonitor monitor;
    List<String> allRepositoryIDs = myFactory.getRepositoryIDs();
    for (String repositoryID : allRepositoryIDs)
    {
        idocRepository = myFactory.getRepository(repositoryID);
        monitor = idocRepository!=null ? idocRepository.getMonitor() : null;
        ...
    }
    Since:
    IDocLibrary 3.0.7
    See Also:
    IDocFactory.getRepositoryIDs(), IDocFactory.getRepository(repositoryID), IDocRepository.getMonitor()
